Commissioner Khehla Sitole on Thursday conceded police have made too many promises regarding the murder of former Banana Banana goalkeeper Senzo Meyiwa, more than three years ago “Yes, I think we have made too many promises… actually, today I’m personally involved in dealing with certain information,” Sitole told MPs while briefing Parliament’s portfolio committee on police on the SA Police Service annual performance plan. READ MORE: Longwe Twala denies involvement in Meyiwa murder READ MORE: My son watched it all – Kelly Khumalo details Meyiwa’s last hours